    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I need some help with a professional email. I'm an HR manager at a logistics company and I have to write a formal reprimand to an employee. They've been about 15 minutes late to every shift for the last two weeks. I need it to be firm and professional but not like, unnecessarily aggressive. Can you draft something for me?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Subject: Urgent: Formal Notice of Repeated Tardiness\n\nDear [Employee's Name],\n\nI am writing to address the ongoing issue of your tardiness, which has occurred on six different occasions over the past two weeks, with you arriving at least 15 minutes late each time. As stated in our company attendance policy, consistent punctuality is expected from all employees and your recent pattern violates this requirement.\n\nPlease understand that timely attendance is crucial for the smooth operation of our logistics services, and such behavior hinders overall productivity. Your immediate attention to this matter is required, and I urge you to exhibit a more disciplined attitude toward maintaining scheduled work hours.\n\nI believe this serves as a reminder of the importance of adhering to the terms of your employment schedule. Further instances of tardiness could lead to more severe disciplinary action.\n\nThank you for taking immediate steps to rectify this situation.\n\nBest regards,\n\n[Your Full Name]  \n[Your Position]  \n[Contact Information]  \n[Logistics Company Name]",
